						               													<description>From the 2011 Ludo Award Winner Marcos Macri, a new game for fast and vicious fun. Imagine you are traveling by train with a friend and then, in one connection, your luggage is opened any its contents spilled and mixed with the others passengers waiting the same connection. And at this same time, the train arrives. And so your quiet voyage turns into a mayhem as you need to find your things, put in your bag, sit in a good place at the train, and guarantee you can continue your conversation with your best friend: Yourself.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player assumes two secret roles and receives a hand of cards that can be objects for either of his roles or of other characters on the train. On each turn, a player has five actions points that can be used for:&amp;#10;- Put an item in a bag (Not necessary his own)&amp;#10;- Exchange an item from a bag to another bag&amp;#10;- Look at an hidden item in a bag&amp;#10;- Exchange hands with other player&amp;#10;- Buy clothes&amp;#10;- Exchange characters place on the train&amp;#10;When a bag has five items on it, it is automatically closed and that character can no longer be target of any action, except to change places with another character whose bag is also closed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When the number of closed bags is equal to the number of players, the game ends and points are awarded to each player accordingly to theirs characters:&amp;#10;- Sitting position in the train&amp;#10;- If they are sitting near each other&amp;#10;- Own items on bag&amp;#10;- Cloth on bag&amp;#10;- Pair of other character item on bag.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
